Modifications by ForgeGuard include (non-exhaustive): non-blocking startup with
background model warmup and readiness endpoints, optional bearer-token
authentication, a React web console, Jetson (arm64/L4T) and CUDA cu128 images,
a renamed Helm chart, and removal of bare-metal run support in favor of
container-only distribution. See CHANGELOG.md for details.

This product uses the Kokoro-82M text-to-speech model
(https://huggingface.co/hexgrad/Kokoro-82M) by hexgrad, licensed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0, together with the kokoro
(https://github.com/hexgrad/kokoro) and misaki
(https://github.com/hexgrad/misaki) libraries.

Portions of the inference code are adapted from StyleTTS2
(https://github.com/yl4579/StyleTTS2), licensed under the MIT License.
